C++ usage in emCore (236 occurrences in headers, 81 in .cpp files):
  - emRec.h: emArray<char> used for serialization buffers (emRecMemWriter, emRecMemReader)
  - emProcess.h (line 87): emArray<emString> for args and extraEnv parameters
  - emPanel.h: emArray<emString> for DecodeIdentity/EncodeIdentity
  - emImage.h: includes emArray.h (emImage stores pixel data)
  - emInput.h (line ~60): emArray<emInputEvent> for event storage
  - emScalarField.h (line ~106): emArray<emUInt64> for scale mark intervals
  - emListBox.h: emArray<int> for selected indices
  - emFileSelectionBox.h: emArray<emString> for selected names and filters
  - emStd2.h: emArray<emString> used in utility functions
  - emFileDialog.h: emArray<emString> for file paths
  - emScreen.h: emArray used for monitor/window lists
  - emLinearLayout.h: emArray for child constraints
  - emPackLayout.h: emArray for cell info
  - emRec.cpp (lines 129,135): emArray<char> buf for TryLoadFromMem/SaveToMem
  - emProcess.cpp (lines 87,94-97): emArray<emString> for args, env; emArray<char> for envBlock, cmd
  - emPanel.cpp (lines 228,249,285,287): emArray<emString> for identity encoding/decoding
  - emColorField.cpp (line 217): emArray<emUInt64> for percentIntervals
  - emFileSelectionBox.cpp (lines 140,147,156,158,246): emArray<emString> for selected names, filters

Rust equivalents found:
  - emArray<T> broadly maps to Vec<T>
  - GetCount: Vec::len() -- used pervasively across the Rust codebase
  - SetCount: Vec::resize() / Vec::truncate()
  - Compact: Vec::shrink_to_fit()
  - Get/operator[]: Vec index operator or .get()
  - GetWritable: direct mutable access (no COW in Rust)
  - Add: Vec::push() / Vec::extend()
  - Insert: Vec::insert()
  - Remove: Vec::remove() / Vec::drain()
  - Clear: Vec::clear()
  - IsEmpty: Vec::is_empty()
  - Sort: Vec::sort_by() -- see src/emCore/emClipRects.rs:337
  - BinarySearch: Vec::binary_search_by() or slice::binary_search()
  - GetSubArray: slice indexing [a..b] or .to_vec()
  - Extract: Vec::drain(range).collect()
  - Replace: Vec::splice()
  - emSortArray: slice::sort_by() -- no custom needed
  - emBinarySearch: slice::binary_search_by()
  - Iterator: standard Rust iterators (.iter(), .iter_mut(), for loops)
  - TuningLevel: no Rust equivalent needed (Rust has no COW array; Vec manages capacity automatically)
  - COW (copy-on-write): no Rust equivalent (Vec uses move semantics / Clone)
  - GetDataRefCount/MakeNonShared: no Rust equivalent (single-owner by design)
  Representative Vec usage locations:
    - src/emCore/emPainterDrawList.rs:69 -- Vec<(f64,f64)> for vertices
    - src/emCore/emEngine.rs:62-63 -- Vec<SignalId>, Vec<EngineId> for scheduler queues
    - src/emCore/emLinearLayout.rs:311-355 -- Vec for constraints and index lists
    - src/emCore/emScalarField.rs:106 -- Vec<u64> for scale_mark_intervals
    - src/emCore/emListBox.rs:367 -- Vec<String> for items
    - src/emCore/emScreen.rs:23 -- Vec<MonitorInfo>
    - src/emCore/emInputState.rs:16 -- Vec<(u64, f64, f64)> for touches

Coverage gaps:
  - BinaryInsert, BinaryInsertIfNew, BinaryInsertOrReplace, BinaryReplace, BinaryRemove,
    BinaryRemoveByKey: no direct Rust equivalents found in the codebase, but these can be
    trivially composed from binary_search_by + insert/remove. Not found in use in the ported
    Rust code so far.
  - PointerToIndex: not directly needed in Rust (use index-based iteration)
  - emArray<OBJ>::Iterator: Rust uses standard iterators; no custom Iterator type needed.

